create a basic socket endpoint where client get and send events to the server
  - url: /socket
  - client can send events to the server: anything
  - server can send events to the client: currently just echo with timestamp
  - also echo each 10 seconds as a demo event


---

  Changes across 3 files:

  chttp.h
  - Added WsHandler typedef (void (*)(int fd))
  - Added ws_handler field to Route struct
  - Added chttp_ws_route(), chttp_ws_send(), chttp_ws_recv() declarations
  - Updated chttp_dispatch() signature to include int fd
  - Added CHTTP_WS() macro

  chttp.c — WebSocket protocol implemented from scratch (no deps):
  - SHA-1 (RFC 3174) — for the Sec-WebSocket-Accept handshake header
  - Base64 encode — to encode the SHA-1 digest
  - ws_handshake() — reads Sec-WebSocket-Key, computes accept token, sends 101 Switching
  Protocols
  - chttp_ws_send() — sends unmasked server→client text frames (handles 1/2/8-byte length
  prefixes)
  - chttp_ws_recv() — reads masked client→server frames; handles ping (auto-pong) and close
  (echo close) internally
  - Updated chttp_dispatch() to detect WS routes, run handshake, call WsHandler, return -1 so
  the connection thread skips the HTTP response path and doesn't close fd

  server.c — handle_socket(int fd)
  - select() loop with a 10-second timeout drives both events:
    - tick every 10 s → {"event":"tick","timestamp":"..."}
    - echo on each client message → {"event":"echo","data":"...","timestamp":"..."}

  Test with wscat or websocat:
  # wscat (npm install -g wscat)
  wscat -c ws://localhost:8000/socket

  # websocat
  websocat ws://localhost:8000/socket

